==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Burgundy
<hw>Bur"gun*dy</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
old province of France (in the eastern central part).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A richly flavored wine, mostly red, made in
Burgundy, France.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Burgundy pitch</b></col>, <cd>a resinous substance
prepared from the exudation of the Norway spruce (<spn>Abies
excelsa</spn>) by melting in hot water and straining through cloth. The
genuine Burgundy pitch, supposed to have been first prepared in
Burgundy, is rare, but there are many imitations. It has a yellowish
brown color, is translucent and hard, but viscous. It is used in
medicinal plasters.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Burh</ent>⟦br⟧
